Notes: All participants were tested in three phases: run-in, phase 1 and phase 2. The run-in phase was the no-drug control phase (1–3 days), and phases 1 and 2 defined the dose administrations of 30 mg or 60 mg domperidone daily (as 10 mg or 20 mg every 8 h). The duration of phases 1 and 2 was between 1 and 2 weeks. Following the run-in period, mothers were randomized to either the 30-mg or 60-mg daily dose in phase 1 and to the alternate dose in phase 2.
